                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14471455" author="nagai_masato" created="Sat, 2 Jul 2011 08:22:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;contains space characters &lt;br/&gt;
contains double quoted strings have space characters&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471524" author="nagai_masato" created="Sat, 2 Jul 2011 11:23:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When JAVA_OPTS is -Daprop=&quot;a value&quot;, &quot;%JAVA_OPTS&quot; means &quot;-Daprop=&quot;a value&quot;&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
So the following part of startGroovy.bat (line 223) throws the error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if &quot;%JAVA_OPTS%&quot; == &quot;&quot; set JAVA_OPTS=&quot;-Xmx128m&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch changes startGroovy.bat to use GROOVY_OPTS local variable for local options instead of JAVA_OPTS that is commonly used by other programs. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471440" author="nagai_masato" created="Sun, 3 Jul 2011 08:01:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also attached a small test program.&lt;br/&gt;
By the way, is there nobody can verify this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471512" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2011 14:52:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Paul, can you check this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471514" author="paulk" created="Tue, 26 Jul 2011 23:44:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch applied, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
